Jeff Wicks, News24Hlaudi Motsoeneng (File, Jenni Evans, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - The ANC Youth league in KwaZulu-Natal has announced that they will support a move to vote controversial SABC corporate affairs head Hlaudi Motsoeneng to the party&rsquo;s National Executive Committee at the elective conference in 2017. Motsoeneng is expected to deliver a guest address at an ANCYL KZN lecture on economic freedom. &nbsp;Thinta Cibane, the ANCYL secretary general in the eThekwini region, said that the provincial structure would support the elevation of Motsoeneng to the NEC. &ldquo;Comrade Hlaudi we misled you when we asked you to come here and deliver this lecture.&ldquo;We want to announce that we will support your name at the ANC NEC conference in 2017&hellip;we want to give you a five-year term as the member of the ANC so that you can be deployed to an even more strategic position in the Cabinet as a minister,&rdquo; he said. &nbsp;&ldquo;We know that with you in the NEC there will be no more votes of no confidence,&rdquo; he added. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.